e under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subchapter}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ shall be administered by the department of revenue, the assessor, and other county officials as provided in }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subchapter}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{.}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{b.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{The reimbursement of rent constituting property taxes paid under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subchapter}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ shall be administered by the department of health and human services as provided in }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subchapter}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{.}}}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7425.16}}}{]}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2018 Acts, ch 1041, \'a7127}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2020 Acts, ch 1063, \'a7231}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2021 Acts, ch 41, \'a715, 36}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2021 Acts, ch 174, \'a718, 34, 39}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2023 Acts, ch 19, \'a71128}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2023 Acts, ch 71, \'a742, 48, 49}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a725B.7}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 427.9}}}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj}{2023 amendment to subsection 1 applies retroactively to assessment years beginning on or after January 1, 2023; }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{2023 Acts, ch 71, \'a749}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{425.17}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E7_2E4_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E7_2E4_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Definitions.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{As used in }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subchapter}}}{, unless the context otherwise requires:}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{1.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fBase year\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ means the calendar year last ending before the claim is filed.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{a.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fClaimant\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ means any of the following:}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{(1)}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{A person filing a claim for credit under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subchapter}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ who has attained the age of sixty-five years but who has not attained the age of seventy years on or before December 31 of the base year, a person filing a claim for credit or reimbursement under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subchapter}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ who is totally disabled and was totally disabled on or before December 31 of the base year, or a person filing a claim for reimbursement under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subchapter}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ who has attained the age of sixty-five years on or before December 31 of the base year and who is domiciled in this state at the time the claim is filed or at the time of the person\u8217\'3fs death in the case of a claim filed by the executor or administrator of the claimant\u8217\'3fs estate.}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{(2)}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{A person filing a claim for credit or reimbursement under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subchapter}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ who has attained the age of twenty-three years on or before December 31 of the base year or was a head of household on December 31 of the base year, as defined in the }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Internal Revenue Code}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, but has not attained the age or disability status described in subparagraph (1) or the age status and eligibility criteria of subparagraph (3), and is domiciled in this state at the time the claim is filed or at the time of the person\u8217\'3fs death in the case of a claim filed by the executor or administrator of the claimant\u8217\'3fs estate, and was not claimed as a dependent on any other person\u8217\'3fs tax return for the base year.}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{(3)}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{A person filing a claim for credit under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subchapter}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ who has attained the age of seventy years on or before December 31 of the base year, who has a household income of less than two hundred fifty percent of the federal poverty level, as defined by the most recently revised poverty income guidelines published by the United States department of health and human services, and is domiciled in this state at the time the claim is filed or at the time of the person\u8217\'3fs death in the case of a claim filed by the executor or administrator of the claimant\u8217\'3fs estate.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{b.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fClaimant\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ under paragraph }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fa\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ includes a vendee in possession under a contract for deed and may include one or more joint tenants or tenants in common. In the case of a claim for rent constituting property taxes paid, the claimant shall have rented the property during any part of the base year. In the case of a claim for property taxes due, the claimant shall have occupied the property during any part of the fiscal year beginning July 1 of the base year. If a homestead is occupied by two or more persons, and more than one person is able to qualify as a claimant, the persons may each file a claim based upon each person\u8217\'3fs income and rent constituting property taxes paid or property taxes due.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{3.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fGross rent\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ means rental paid at arm\u8217\'3fs length for the right of occupancy of a homestead or manufactured or mobile home, including rent for space occupied by a manufactured or mobile home not to exceed one acre. If the department of health and human services determines that the landlord and tenant have not dealt with each other at arm\u8217\'3fs length, and the department of health and human services is satisfied that the gross rent charged was excessive, the department of health and human services shall adjust the gross rent to a reasonable amount as determined by the department of health and human services.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{4.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fHomestead\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ means the dwelling owned or rented and actually used as a home by the claimant during the period specified in }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{subsection 2}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, and so much of the land surrounding it including one or more contiguous lots or tracts of land, as is reasonably necessary for use of the dwelling as a home, and may consist of a part of a multidwelling or multipurpose building and a part of the land upon which it is built. It does not include personal property except that a manufactured or mobile home may be a homestead. Any dwelling or a part of a multidwelling or multipurpose building which is exempt from taxation, except for an exemption under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 425.1A}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, does not qualify as a homestead under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subchapter}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{. However, solely for purposes of claimants living in a property and receiving reimbursement for rent constituting property taxes paid immediately before the property becomes tax exempt, and continuing to live in it after it becomes tax exempt, the property shall continue to be classified as a homestead. A homestead must be located in this state. When a person is confined in a nursing home, extended-care facility, or hospital, the person shall be considered as occupying or living in the person\u8217\'3fs homestead if the person is the owner of the homestead and the person maintains the homestead and does not lease, rent, or otherwise receive profits from other persons for the use of the homestead.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{5.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fHousehold\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ means a claimant and the claimant\u8217\'3fs spouse if living with the claimant at any time during the base year. }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fLiving with\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ refers to domicile and does not include a temporary visit.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{6.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fHousehold income\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ means all income of the claimant and the claimant\u8217\'3fs spouse in a household and actual monetary contributions received from any other person living with the claimant during their respective twelve-month income tax accounting periods ending with or during the base year.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{7.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fIncome\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ means the sum of Iowa net income as defined in }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 422.7}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, plus all of the following to the extent not already included in Iowa net income:}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{capital gains; alimony; child support money; cash public assistance and relief, except property tax relief granted under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subchapter}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; amount of in-kind assistance for housing expenses; total amounts received from a governmental or other pension or retirement plan, including defined benefit or defined contribution plans; annuities; individual retirement accounts; plans maintained or contributed to by an employer, or maintained or contributed to by a self-employed person as an employer; deferred compensation plans or any earnings attributable to the deferred compensation plans; income received pursuant to a farm tenancy agreement covering real property; railroad retirement benefits; payments received under the federal }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Social Security Act}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, except child insurance benefits received by a member of the claimant\u8217\'3fs household; military retirement and veterans\u8217\'3f disability pensions; interest received from a state or federal government or any of its instrumentalities; workers\u8217\'3f compensation; and the gross amount of disability income or \u8220\'3floss of time\u8221\'3f insurance. }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fIncome\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ does not include gifts from nongovernmental sources, or surplus foods or other relief in kind supplied by a governmental agency. In determining income, net operating losses and net capital losses shall not be considered.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{8.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fProperty taxes due\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ means property taxes including any special assessments, but exclusive of delinquent interest and charges for services, due on a claimant\u8217\'3fs homestead in this state, but includes only property taxes for which the claimant is liable and which will actually be paid by the claimant. However, if the claimant is a person whose property taxes have been suspended under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{sections 427.8}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ and }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{427.9}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fproperty taxes due\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ means property taxes including any special assessments, but exclusive of delinquent interest and charges for services, due on a claimant\u8217\'3fs homestead in this state, but includes only property taxes for which the claimant is liable and which would have to be paid by the claimant if the payment of the taxes has not been suspended pursuant to }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{sections 427.8}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ and }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{427.9}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{. }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fProperty taxes due\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ shall be computed with no deduction for any credit under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subchapter}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ or for any homestead credit allowed under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{subchapter I}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{. Each claim shall be based upon the taxes due during the fiscal year next following the base year. If a homestead is owned by two or more persons as joint tenants or tenants in common, and one or more persons are not members of claimant\u8217\'3fs household, }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fproperty taxes due\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ is that part of property taxes due on the homestead which equals the ownership percentage of the claimant and the claimant\u8217\'3fs household. The county treasurer shall include with the tax receipt a statement that if the owner of the property is eighteen years of age or over, the person may be eligible for the credit allowed under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subchapter}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{. If a homestead is an integral part of a farm, the claimant may use the total property taxes due for the larger unit. If a homestead is an integral part of a multidwelling or multipurpose building the property taxes due for the purpose of }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subsection}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ shall be prorated to reflect the portion which the value of the property that the household occupies as its homestead is to the value of the entire structure. For purposes of }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subsection}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3funit\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ refers to that parcel of property covered by a single tax statement of which the homestead is a part.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{9.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fRent constituting property taxes paid\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ means twenty-three percent of the gross rent actually paid in cash or its equivalent during the base year by the claimant or the claimant\u8217\'3fs household solely for the right of occupancy of their homestead in the base year, and which rent constitutes the basis, in the succeeding year, of a claim for reimbursement under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subchapter}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ by the claimant.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{10.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fSpecial assessment\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ means an unpaid special assessment certified pursuant to }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{chapter 384, subchapter IV}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{. The claimant may include as a portion of the taxes due during the fiscal year next following the base year an amount equal to the unpaid special assessment installment due, plus interest, during the fiscal year next following the base year.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{11.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fTotally disabled\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ means the inability to engage in any substantial gainful employment by reason of any medically determinable physical or mental impairment which can be expected to result in death or which has lasted or is reasonably expected to last for a continuous period of not less than twelve months.}}}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7425.17}}}{; }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{82 Acts, ch 1214, \'a71, 2, 4}}}{]}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{88 Acts, ch 1139, \'a72, 3}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 89 Acts, ch 233, \'a71}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 90 Acts, ch 1250, \'a76}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 91 Acts, ch 191, \'a719, 124}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 92 Acts, ch 1016, \'a741}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{; }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/acts//CH0000.pdf" }{\fldrslt \f5 \fs18{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\cf5{92 Acts, 2nd Ex, ch 1001, \'a7220, 225}}}}}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 93 Acts, ch 156, \'a71, 2}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 93 Acts, ch 180, \'a74, 15, 16, 22, 23}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 94 Acts, ch 1125, \'a71, 2, 5}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 94 Acts, ch 1165, \'a726, 50}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 99 Acts, ch 152, \'a713, 40}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2001 Acts, ch 153, \'a715}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2001 Acts, ch 176, \'a780}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2003 Acts, ch 145, \'a7286}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2011 Acts, ch 25, \'a789}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2015 Acts, ch 109, \'a78, 75}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2018 Acts, ch 1041, \'a7127}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2019 Acts, ch 24, \'a751}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2021 Acts, ch 41, \'a716, 36}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2021 Acts, ch 177, \'a7125, 131}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2023 Acts, ch 19, \'a71129}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2023 Acts, ch 71, \'a743, 48, 49}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2023 Acts, ch 115, \'a748 \u8211\'3f 50}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a725B.7}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 425.23}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 425.24}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 425.39}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 425.40}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 427.9}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 435.22}}}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj}{2021 amendment to subsection 2 applies to claims under }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{chapter 425, subchapter II}}}{, filed on or after January 1, 2022; }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{2021 Acts, ch 177, \'a7131}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj}{2023 amendment to subsections 4 and 8 applies retroactively to assessment years beginning on or after January 1, 2023; }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{2023 Acts, ch 71, \'a749}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj}{2023 amendment to subsection 7 applies to claims under }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{chapter 425, subchapter II}}}{, for credits against property taxes due and payable in fiscal years beginning on or after July 1, 2024; }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{2023 Acts, ch 115, \'a750}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{425.18}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E7_2E5_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E7_2E5_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Right to file a claim.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{The right to file a claim for reimbursement or credit under }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subchapter}}}{ may be exercised by the claimant or on behalf of a claimant by the claimant\u8217\'3fs legal guardian, spouse, or attorney, or by the executor or administrator of the claimant\u8217\'3fs estate. If a claimant dies after having filed a claim for reimbursement for rent constituting property taxes paid, the amount of the reimbursement may be paid to another member of the household as determined by the department of health and human services. If the claimant was the only member of the household, the reimbursement may be paid to the claimant\u8217\'3fs executor or administrator, but if neither is appointed and qualified within one year from the date of the filing of the claim, the reimbursement shall escheat to the state. If a claimant dies after having filed a claim for credit for property taxes due, the amount of credit shall be paid as if the claimant had not died.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7425.18}}}{; }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{82 Acts, ch 1214, \'a73, 4}}}{]}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{83 Acts, ch 111, \'a71, 4}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2015 Acts, ch 109, \'a79, 75}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2018 Acts, ch 1041, \'a7127}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2021 Acts, ch 41, \'a717, 36}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2021 Acts, ch 174, \'a719, 34, 39}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2023 Acts, ch 19, \'a71130}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a725B.7}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 427.9}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{425.19}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E7_2E6_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E7_2E6_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Claim and credit or reimbursement.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{Subject to the limitations provided in }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subchapter}}}{, a claimant may annually claim a credit for property taxes due during the fiscal year next following the base year or claim a reimbursement for rent constituting property taxes paid in the base year. The amount of the credit for property taxes due for a homestead shall be paid on June 15 of each year from the elderly and disabled property tax credit fund under }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 425.39, subsection 1}}}{, by the director of revenue to the county treasurer who shall credit the money received against the amount of the property taxes due and payable on the homestead of the claimant and the amount of the reimbursement for rent constituting property taxes paid shall be paid by the director of health and human services to the claimant from the reimbursement fund under }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 425.39, subsection 2}}}{, on or before December 31 of each year.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7425.19}}}{]}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{83 Acts, ch 172, \'a74}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 99 Acts, ch 152, \'a714, 40}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2018 Acts, ch 1041, \'a7127}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2021 Acts, ch 41, \'a718, 36}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2023 Acts, ch 19, \'a71131}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a725B.7}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 427.9}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{425.20}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E7_2E7_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E7_2E7_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Filing dates }}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8212\'3f}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ affidavit }}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8212\'3f}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ extension.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{1.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{A claim for reimbursement for rent constituting property taxes paid shall not be paid or allowed, unless the claim is filed with and in the possession of the department of health and human services on or before June 1 of the year following the base year.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{A claim for credit for property taxes due shall not be paid or allowed unless the claim is filed with the county treasurer between January 1 and June 1, both dates inclusive, immediately preceding the fiscal year during which the property taxes are due. However, in case of sickness, absence, or other disability of the claimant, or if in the judgment of the county treasurer good cause exists, the county treasurer may extend the time for filing a claim for credit through March 31 of the fiscal year during which the property taxes are due. The county treasurer shall certify to the director of revenue on or before May 1 of each year the total amount of dollars due for claims allowed.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{3.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{In case of sickness, absence, or other disability of the claimant or if, in the judgment of the director of health and human services good cause exists and the claimant requests an extension, the director of health and human services may extend the time for filing a claim for reimbursement. However, any further time granted shall not extend beyond December 31 of the year following the year in which the claim was required to be filed. Claims filed as a result of }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subsection}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ shall be filed with the director of health and human services who shall provide for the reimbursement of the claim to the claimant.}}}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7425.20}}}{; }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81 Acts 2nd Ex, ch 4, \'a71}}}{]}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{83 Acts, ch 111, \'a72, 4}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 88 Acts, ch 1050, \'a71}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 94 Acts, ch 1125, \'a73, 5}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 94 Acts, ch 1165, \'a727, 50}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 96 Acts, ch 1167, \'a73, 8}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2003 Acts, ch 145, \'a7286}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2018 Acts, ch 1041, \'a792}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2021 Acts, ch 41, \'a719, 36}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2023 Acts, ch 19, \'a71132}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2023 Acts, ch 94, \'a71, 3, 4}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2025 Acts, ch 148, \'a78}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a725B.7}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 427.9}}}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj}{2023 amendment to subsection 2 applies to taxes due and payable in fiscal years beginning on or after July 1, 2023; }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{2023 Acts, ch 94, \'a74}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj}{Subsection 3 amended}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{425.21}}}